The paper deals with caching strategies in communication networks, which is a topic that falls under the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The paper specifically focuses on combination networks, which are a type of network topology commonly studied in the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. The use of caches in the relays and users also suggests that the paper may be relevant to the Systems and Control (cs.SI) sub-category. The optimization of network traffic and reduction of congestion is a common theme in the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. Finally, the use of coding techniques to improve caching performance may also make the paper relevant to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CC) sub-category.
